headline: Week’s Best: ‘Big Bang Theory’ Alum’s New Digital Venture
summary: When Kunal Nayyar, an actor best known for playing Raj Koothrappali on The Big Bang Theory, was trying to organize a trip for his parents from India to the U.S., he struggled to keep track of details such as flight numbers and hotel confirmations.  The company he co-founded, IQ121, aims to address those challenges with a secure document storage and sharing system.  Time to cut off the spigot? More than three-quarters of wealthy parents are helping their children pay for big-ticket items such as a down payment on a house or graduate school, while nearly two-thirds are paying for routine expenses such as phone bills and other living costs, according to a new survey from  Ameriprise Financial  All that support may be taking its toll.
